	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Wed Jun 14, 2017 8:11 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Hi-Def NES HDMI Adapter for the NES</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Based on the specific nature of the corruption, with title screen addresses being off by $0200 or $02 and tile numbers being off by $02, it looks like other signals are bleeding into the line between CPU D1 and PPU I/O D1. Could you check the soldering on that line, making sure it isn't bridged to anything?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

